 Editor's note: This story has been updated with additional informationJOHANNESBURG - South African Airways (SAA) said all flights to and from Zimbabwe were cancelled for Saturday. This comes after SAA confirmed that one of its aircraft was unable to operate from Zimbabwe on Saturday morning. The carrier s spokesperson Tlali Tlali said authorities in Harare are yet to give the green light for operations to return to normal.The delayed aircraft is flight SA 025 from Harare to Johannesburg.Tlali has apologised to affected passengers for the inconvenience.eNCA